  volume    =  68,
  number    =  50,
  pages     = "1162--1165",
  abstract  = "On August 1, 2018, the Democratic Republic of the Congo Ministry
               of Health (DRC MoH) declared the tenth outbreak of Ebola virus
               disease (Ebola) in DRC, in the North Kivu province in eastern DRC
               on the border with Uganda, 8 days after another Ebola outbreak
               was declared over in northwest Équateur province. During mid- to
               late-July 2018, a cluster of 26 cases of acute hemorrhagic fever,
