  volume    = "179 Suppl 1",
  number    = "s1",
  pages     = "S92--7",
  abstract  = "In 1995, 316 people became ill with Ebola hemorrhagic fever (EHF)
               in Kikwit, Democratic Republic of the Congo. The exposure source
               was not reported for 55 patients (17\%) at the start of this
               investigation, and it remained unknown for 12 patients after
