  volume    =  8,
  number    =  10,
  pages     = "e1002877",
  abstract  = "Marburg virus (family Filoviridae) causes sporadic outbreaks of
               severe hemorrhagic disease in sub-Saharan Africa. Bats have been
               implicated as likely natural reservoir hosts based most recently
               on an investigation of cases among miners infected in 2007 at the
               Kitaka mine, Uganda, which contained a large population of
